7. What is Checkpoint (CKPT) ? (it also execute every 3 sec)

=> ✅ CKPT makes sure that all changes in memory (SGA → buffer cache) are safely written to datafiles on disk.

	✅ CKPT instruct DBwn to write dirty block into the datafiles (Committed + Uncommitted both). update control file with SCN number. And, update Datafile Headers.

   ✅ CKPT (checkpoint) are 2 types.
	 i). Incremental Checkpoint.  (ii). Full Checkpoint
-----------------------------------------------------------

# Incremental Checkpoint :-

=> ✅ It searched for newly added SCN number, and it writes that new SCN number to 'control file' and update the new SCN number header of the 'datafile'.
-------------------------------------------------------------

# Full Checkpoint :-

=> ✅ It execute, when we do full shutdown or log switch.
		Full Checkpoint is also looks for newly added SCN number, and it writes that new SCN number to 'control file' and update the new SCN number header of the 'datafile'.

		* Full Checkpoint instruct 'DBWN' / 'lazy writer' to write all the 'dirty blocks' into datafile.
-------------------------------------------------------------

7.1. When Does a Checkpoint Happen?
=> Checkpoints can occur in several situations:

	✅ Log Switch → when redo log file switches, checkpoint happens.

	✅ Timeout → after a certain interval (LOG_CHECKPOINT_INTERVAL / FAST_START_MTTR_TARGET).

	✅ Manual → DBA issues ALTER SYSTEM CHECKPOINT;.

	✅ Database close → when shutting down cleanly, checkpoint ensures all data is written.

