=> ✅ ORA-01555 occurs when Oracle cannot provide old data required for read consistency
		 because the undo tablespace information has been overwritten.

	🔹 When ORA-01555 happens (step-by-step)

		👉 A long SELECT query starts

		👉 Oracle notes the SCN

		👉 Other sessions perform UPDATE/DELETE

		👉 Old data is written into UNDO

		👉 UNDO gets overwritten

		👉 SELECT needs old data → not found
